Brik V. Eyre











 Brik V. Eyre



Brik V. Eyre is senior vice president and president, Americas.He also serves as executive sponsor of Baxter Women Leaders, a business  resource group for employees dedicated to creating professional  growth opportunities for women at all levels and stages in their careers  through education, community and networking events, as well as  advocating on behalf of women and women's business issues.Eyre joined the company in 2008 as general manager for BioPharma Solutions, Baxter’s global manufacturing and contract services business. He later served as general manager for Baxter’s U.S. Medication Delivery business, and most recently he was corporate vice president and president of Baxter’s Renal business.Prior to joining Baxter, he held a variety of senior management positions at Cardinal Health, including president of Cardinal’s PreSource Products and Services business.Eyre earned his MBA from the University of Tulsa, and a bachelor’s degree in finance from Utah State University.

















