health care

Biography:
Brik Eyre is corporate vice president and president of hospital products for Baxter International. Baxter is a multinational medical products company with business in more than one hundred countries. Prior to joining Baxter, Brik served in a variety of senior management positions at Cardinal Health. He serves on the executive board of the Northeast Illinois Council of the Boy Scouts of America and is a board member of AdvaMed, the industry association for medical technology. Brik enjoys sports, travel, and his family. He earned his bachelor’s degree in finance from Utah State University and his MBA from the University of Tulsa. Brik and Susan have five children.
















